Island Hopping in the Dutch Caribbean
⠀⠀
_________
⠀⠀
The so-called ABC islands of Aruba, Bonaire and Curaçao lie just north of Venezuala and offer pristine white-sand beaches, crazy wildlife, and breathtaking architecture. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ A travelers dream, these cactus-studded islands have long been part of the Kingdom of the Netherlands, resulting in deep-rooted Dutch heritage mixed with Caribbean ambience. ⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀
The beautiful building pictured? It’s their MALL. Featuring a gorgeous dome top and bright eye-capturing pastel colors, it has become iconic for its Dutch colonial architecture. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀
